msgid "Push access to Weblate git repositories (it pushes tags)"
msgstr "推送存取 Weblate git 儲存庫（它推送標記）"

#: contributing/schemas.rst:2
msgid "Data schemas"
msgstr "資料架構"

#: contributing/schemas.rst:4
msgid ""
"Weblate uses `JSON Schema <https://json-schema.org/>`_ to define layout of "
"external JSON files."
msgstr ""
"Weblate 使用 `JSON Schema <https://json-schema.org/>`_ 來定義外部 JSON 檔案的"
"設定。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:3
msgid "License and copyright"
msgstr "授權與著作權"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:5
msgid ""
"When contributing project code, you agree to put your changes and new code "
"under the repository license, :abbr:`GPL-3.0-or-later (GNU General Public "
"License v3.0 or later)`, unless stated and agreed otherwise. New source "
"files should follow the existing copyright and :abbr:`SPDX (Software Package "
"Data Exchange)` license header style."
msgstr ""
"貢獻專案程式碼時，即表示您同意將變更及新程式碼置於儲存庫的 :abbr:`GPL-3.0-or-"
"later (GNU General Public License v3.0 or later)` 授權條款下，除非另有聲明及"
"協議。新來源檔案應遵循現有的著作權及 :abbr:`SPDX (Software Package Data "
"Exchange)` 授權標頭樣式。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:11
msgid ""
"Use a different license only when there is a deliberate reason, such as "
"files shared with repositories using more permissive licenses."
msgstr ""
"只有在有明確理由時才使用不同的授權，例如檔案會與採用較寬鬆授權的儲存庫共用。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:16
msgid ":doc:`/contributing/license` explains licensing in more details."
msgstr ":doc:`/contributing/license` 會更詳細地說明授權方式。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:19
msgid "Writing a good patch"
msgstr "撰寫良好的修補程式"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:22
msgid "Write separate changes"
msgstr "寫入單獨的變更"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:24
msgid ""
"It is annoying when you get a massive patch that is said to fix 11 odd "
"problems, but discussions and opinions do not agree with 10 of them or 9 of "
"them were already fixed differently. Then the person merging this change "
"needs to extract the single interesting patch from somewhere within the "
"massive pile of sources, and that creates a lot of extra work."
msgstr ""
"獲得一個聲稱修復 11 個古怪問題的補丁令人煩惱，關於該補丁的討論和意見不同意它"
"們中的 10 個算問題，或者認為這些問題中的 9 個已經用另一方式被修復了。然後，合"
"併這一變更的人需要從成堆的原始碼中提取出單一的有趣補丁，而這樣做產生許多額外"
"的工作。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:30
msgid ""
"Preferably, each fix that addresses an issue should be in its own patch/"
"commit with its own description/commit message stating exactly what they "
"correct so that all changes can be selectively applied by the maintainer or "
"other interested parties."
msgstr ""
"建議每項問題修正都放在個別的修補程式或提交中，並附上自己的說明或提交訊息，明"
"確指出修正內容，讓維護者或其他相關人員能選擇性地套用各項變更。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:35
msgid ""
"Furthermore, separate changes enable bisecting much better for tracking "
"issues and regression in the future."
msgstr "此外，分開提交變更也更有利於使用二分搜尋，追蹤未來的問題與回歸。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:39 security/release-artifacts.rst:63
msgid "Documentation"
msgstr "說明文件"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:41
msgid ""
"Documentation can be a tedious task; however, it is necessary for someone to "
"complete it. It makes things a lot easier if you submit the documentation "
"together with code changes. Please remember to document methods, complex "
"code blocks, or user-visible features."
msgstr ""
"撰寫說明文件可能很繁瑣，但仍必須有人完成。若能將說明文件與程式碼變更一併提"
"交，事情會容易許多。請記得記錄方法、複雜的程式碼區塊及使用者可見的功能。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:52
msgid "Test cases"
msgstr "測試案例"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:54
msgid ""
"The tests allow us to quickly verify that the features are working as they "
"are supposed to. To maintain this situation and improve it, all new features "
"and functions that are added need to be tested in the test suite. Every "
"feature that is added should get at least one valid test case that verifies "
"that it works as documented."
msgstr ""
"測試可讓我們快速確認功能是否依預期運作。為維持並改善這種情況，所有新增的功能"
"與函式都必須納入測試套件。每項新增功能至少應有一個有效測試案例，驗證其是否依"
"說明文件運作。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:65
msgid "Commit messages"
msgstr "提交訊息"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:67
msgid ""
"Git commits should follow `Conventional Commits <https://"
"www.conventionalcommits.org/>`_ specification."
msgstr ""
"Git 提交應該遵守 `Conventional Commits <https://www.conventionalcommits.org/"
">`_ 規範。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:71
msgid "Type checking"
msgstr "類型檢查"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:73
msgid ""
"Any new code should utilize :pep:`484` type hints. We are "
"using :program:`mypy` to check them because it has a Django plugin that "
"makes type checking of Django apps practical."
msgstr ""
"任何新程式碼都應使用 :pep:`484` 型別提示。我們在使用 :program:`mypy` 進行檢查"
"（因為它有一個讓 Django 應用的型別檢查變得實際可行的 Django 外掛）。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:77
msgid ""
"New and changed code should not introduce new :program:`mypy` failures where "
"current Django typing support makes that practical. The code base is not yet "
"completely covered by type annotations, and some Django constructs are "
"difficult to annotate precisely. CI therefore enforces :program:`mypy` only "
"for selected modules and reports other findings separately."
msgstr ""
"在目前 Django 型別支援可行的範圍內，新增及變更後的程式碼不應引入新"
"的 :program:`mypy` 失敗。程式碼庫目前尚未完全涵蓋型別註解，且部分 Django 結構"
"難以精確加上註解。因此，CI 僅對選取的模組強制執行 :program:`mypy`，並另外回報"
"其他發現。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:84
msgid "Coding standard and linting the code"
msgstr "編碼標準和程式碼檢查"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:86
msgid ""
"The code should follow :pep:`8` coding guidelines and should be formatted "
"using :program:`ruff` code formatter."
msgstr ""
"程式碼應該符合 :pep:`8` 變成指導原則，並且應該使用 :program:`ruff` 程式碼格式"
"化器來格式化。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:89
msgid ""
"To check the code quality, you can use :program:`ruff`, its configuration is "
"stored in :file:`pyproject.toml`."
msgstr ""
"要檢查程式碼品質，您可以使用 :program:`ruff`，其設定儲存"
"在 :file:`pyproject.toml` 中。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:92
msgid ""
"When suppressing a :program:`ruff` diagnostic, prefer ``# ruff: ignore[rule-"
"name]`` with the human-readable rule name. Place the comment on the line "
"above the logical statement or block when that does not broaden the "
"suppression scope. Keep the comment inline when moving it would change the "
"scope, affect import sorting, or get between another tool's ``disable-next`` "
"comment and the code it targets."
msgstr ""
"抑制 :program:`ruff` 診斷時，請優先使用含有人類可讀規則名稱的 ``# ruff: "
"ignore[rule-name]``。如果不會擴大抑制範圍，請將註解放在邏輯陳述式或區塊的上一"
"行。若移動註解會變更範圍、影響匯入排序，或插入另一個工具的 ``disable-next`` "
"註解與其目標程式碼之間，則應將註解保留在行內。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:99
msgid ""
"The easiest approach to enforce all this is to install :program:`prek`. This "
"is a third-party reimplementation of the `pre-commit`_ tool used by Weblate. "
"It is included in the development dependencies declared "
"in :file:`pyproject.toml`, so installing those dependencies "
"makes :program:`prek` available."
msgstr ""
"要落實上述規則，最簡單的方式是安裝 :program:`prek`。它是 Weblate 所用 `pre-"
"commit`_ 工具的第三方重新實作，已包含在 :file:`pyproject.toml` 宣告的開發相依"
"套件中，因此安裝這些相依套件後即可使用 :program:`prek`。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:104
msgid "To check all files manually, run:"
msgstr "要手動檢查所有檔案，請執行："

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:110
msgid ""
"If you prefer the original :program:`pre-commit` client, it uses the same "
"configuration from :file:`.pre-commit-config.yaml`."
msgstr ""
"如果偏好原版 :program:`pre-commit` 客戶端，它使用來自 :file:`.pre-commit-"
"config.yaml` 的相同設定。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:116
msgid "Coding securely"
msgstr "安全地編寫程式碼"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:118
msgid ""
"Any code for Weblate should be written with `Security by Design Principles`_ "
"in mind."
msgstr ""
"編寫 Weblate 的任何代碼應該時刻記得 `Security by Design Principles`_ （由設計"
"原理來提供安全性）。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:124
msgid "AI guidelines"
msgstr "AI 指導原則"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:126
msgid ""
"When contributing content to the project, you give us permission to use it "
"as-is, and you must make sure you are allowed to distribute it to us. By "
"submitting a change to us, you agree that the changes can and should be "
"adopted by the project and get redistributed under the project license. "
"Authors should be explicitly aware that the burden is on them to ensure no "
"unlicensed code is submitted to the project."
msgstr ""
"在向專案貢獻內容時，您同意我們照原樣使用它，且您必須確保您被允許將它分發給我"
"們。向我們提交改動代表您同意這些變更能夠並應被本專案採用，並在本專案授權下再"
"次分發。作者應明確知道確保沒有未經許可的程式碼被提交至本專案的責任在於作者。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:133
msgid "This is independent of whether AI is used or not."
msgstr "這無關是否使用 AI。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:135
msgid ""
"When contributing a pull request, you should, of course, always make sure "
"that the proposal is of good quality and the best effort that follows our "
"guidelines. A basic rule of thumb is that if someone can spot that the "
"contribution was made with the help of AI, you have more work to do."
msgstr ""
"提交 Pull Request 時，當然應盡力確保提案品質良好並遵循我們的指引。基本原則"
"是：若別人看得出貢獻內容是在 AI 協助下完成，您就還需要進一步修改。"

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:140
msgid ""
"We can accept code written with the help of AI into the project, but the "
"code must still follow coding standards, be written clearly, be documented, "
"feature test cases, and adhere to all the normal requirements we have."
msgstr ""
"本專案可以接受 AI 協助撰寫的程式碼，但程式碼仍須遵循編碼標準、清楚撰寫、具備"
"說明文件與測試案例，並符合所有一般要求。"

#: contributing/start.rst:2
msgid "Starting contributing code to Weblate"
msgstr "開始為 Weblate 貢獻程式碼"

#: contributing/start.rst:4
msgid ""
"Understand the Weblate source code by going "
"through :doc:`code`, :doc:`frontend` and :doc:`internals`."
msgstr ""
"要理解 Weblate 原始碼，請瀏覽 :doc:`code`、 :doc:`frontend` "
"和 :doc:`internals`。"

#: contributing/start.rst:8
msgid "Starting with the codebase"
msgstr "從程式碼庫開始"

#: contributing/start.rst:10
msgid ""
"Familiarize yourself with the Weblate codebase, by having a go at the bugs "
"labelled `good first issue <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/labels/"
"good%20first%20issue>`_."
msgstr ""
"若要熟悉 Weblate 程式碼庫，可以先嘗試處理標有 `good first issue <https://"
"github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/labels/good%20first%20issue>`_ 的問題。"

#: contributing/start.rst:13
msgid ""
"You are welcome to start working on these issues without asking. Just "
"announce that in the issue, so that it's clear that somebody is working on "
"that issue."
msgstr ""
"歡迎直接開始處理這些問題，不必事先詢問。只要在問題中留言告知，讓大家知道已有"
"人著手處理即可。"

#: contributing/start.rst:17
msgid "Running Weblate locally"
msgstr "本機執行 Weblate"

#: contributing/start.rst:19
msgid ""
"The most comfortable approach to get started with Weblate development is to "
"follow :doc:`../admin/install/source`. It will get you a Python environment "
"with editable Weblate sources."
msgstr ""
"開始參與 Weblate 開發最方便的方式，是依照 :doc:`../admin/install/source` 操"
"作。這會建立含可編輯 Weblate 原始碼的 Python 環境。"

#: contributing/start.rst:23
msgid "Clone the Weblate source code:"
msgstr "複製 Weblate 原始碼："

#: contributing/start.rst:30
msgid "Install Weblate and all dependencies useful for development:"
msgstr "安裝 Weblate 和所有對開發有用的相依套件："

#: contributing/start.rst:36
msgid "Start a development server:"
msgstr "啟動開發伺服器："

#: contributing/start.rst:42
msgid ""
"Depending on your configuration, you might also want to start Celery workers:"
msgstr "取決於設定，您也許想啟動 Celery workers："

#: contributing/start.rst:48
msgid "To run tests (see :ref:`local-tests` for more details):"
msgstr "若要執行測試（更多細節請參閱 :ref:`local-tests`）："

#: contributing/start.rst:62
msgid "Running Weblate locally in Docker"
msgstr "在 Docker 中本機執行 Weblate"

#: contributing/start.rst:64
msgid ""
"If you have Docker and the docker-compose-plugin installed, you need an "
"additional tool called ``jq`` which you can install through your favorite "
"package manager. Then, you can spin up the development environment by simply "
"running:"
msgstr ""
"如果您安裝了 Docker 和 docker-compose-plugin，您還需要透過您喜愛的包管理器安"
"裝名為 ``jq`` 的額外工具。之後，只需執行以下指令即可啟動開發環境："

#: contributing/start.rst:72
msgid ""
"It will create a development Docker image and start it. Weblate is running "
"on <http://127.0.0.1:8080/> and you can sign in as the user ``admin`` using "
"``admin`` as the password. The new installation is empty, so you might want "
"to continue with :ref:`adding-projects`."
msgstr ""
"它將新增 Docker 影響並啟動它。 Weblate 執行在 <http://127.0.0.1:8080/> 上，並"
"且您可以以 ``admin`` 為使用者名稱， ``admin`` 為密碼來登入。新的安裝是空的，"
"所以您會想要以 :ref:`adding-projects` 來繼續。"

#: contributing/start.rst:77
msgid ""
"Weblate is configured to use :program:`maildev` container as an e-mail "
"server. The delivered e-mails can be seen at <http://127.0.0.1:1080/>."
msgstr ""
"Weblate 已設定為使用 :program:`maildev` 容器作為電子郵件伺服器。寄送的電子郵"
"件可在 <http://127.0.0.1:1080/> 檢視。"

#: contributing/start.rst:80
msgid ""
"The :file:`Dockerfile` and :file:`docker-compose.yml` for this are located "
"in the :file:`dev-docker` directory. For easier access to the database "
"during development, the container running PostgreSQL is exposed on port "
"``5433``."
msgstr ""
"相關的 :file:`Dockerfile` 與 :file:`docker-compose.yml` 位於 :file:`dev-"
"docker` 目錄。為方便開發期間存取資料庫，執行 PostgreSQL 的容器會在 ``5433`` "
"連接埠提供服務。"

#: contributing/start.rst:84
msgid ""
"The script also accepts some parameters, to execute tests, run it with the "
"``test`` parameter and then specify any :djadmin:`django:test` parameters, "
"for example running only tests in the ``weblate.machine`` module:"
msgstr ""
"指令碼還接受一些引數，要執行測試，以 ``test`` 引數來執行，然後指定任"
"何 :djadmin:`django:test` 引數，例如，只在 ``weblate.machine`` 模組中執行測"
"試："

#: contributing/start.rst:94
msgid ""
"Be careful that your Docker containers are up and running before running the "
"tests. You can check that by running the ``docker ps`` command."
msgstr ""
"小心在執行測試前您的 Docker 容易活動並執行。您可以通過執行 ``docker ps`` 指令"
"來檢查。"

#: contributing/start.rst:97
msgid "To display the logs:"
msgstr "展示日誌："

#: contributing/start.rst:103
msgid "To stop the background containers, run:"
msgstr "為了停止背景容器，執行："

#: contributing/start.rst:109
msgid ""
"Running the script without arguments will re-create the Docker container and "
"restart it."
msgstr "執行沒有任何參數的指令碼將重建 Docker 容器並重啟動它。"

#: contributing/start.rst:113
msgid ""
"This container is not suitable for production use. Security is sacrificed to "
"make the development easier."
msgstr "此容器不適合正式環境使用。為簡化開發工作，其安全性有所取捨。"

#: contributing/start.rst:119
msgid "Bootstrapping your devel instance"
msgstr "引導您的開發執行個體"

#: contributing/start.rst:121
msgid ""
"You might want to use :wladmin:`import_demo` to create demo translations "
"and :wladmin:`createadmin` to make an admin user."
msgstr ""
"您可以使用 :wladmin:`import_demo` 建立示範翻譯，並使"
"用 :wladmin:`createadmin` 建立管理員使用者。"

#: contributing/start.rst:124
msgid ""
"If you have :ref:`billing` installed as well, you can "
"use :wladmin:`billing_demo` to create a demo billing project."
msgstr ""
"若也安裝了 :ref:`billing`，可以使用 :wladmin:`billing_demo` 建立示範帳務專"
"案。"

#: contributing/start.rst:128
msgid "Coding Weblate with PyCharm"
msgstr "使用 PyCharm 為 Weblate 編寫程式碼"

#: contributing/start.rst:130
msgid ""
"PyCharm is a known IDE for Python, here are some guidelines to help you set "
"up your Weblate project in it."
msgstr ""
"PyCharm 是 Python 的著名 IDE，這裡有一些幫助您在其中建立您的 Weblate 專案的指"
"導原則。"

#: contributing/start.rst:133
msgid ""
"Considering you have just cloned the GitHub repository to a folder, just "
"open it with PyCharm. Once the IDE is open, the first step is to specify the "
"interpreter you want to use:"
msgstr ""
"考慮到您剛剛將 GitHub 儲存庫複製到一個資料夾中，只需使用 PyCharm 開啟它。一"
"旦 IDE 開啟，第一步要做的是指定您想要使用的直譯器："

#: contributing/start.rst:139
msgid ""
"Select the :file:`.venv` environment created by ``uv sync --all-extras --"
"dev`` to match the command-line development setup. You can also let PyCharm "
"create a Python environment for you, but the uv-managed environment is "
"preferred:"
msgstr ""
"選取由 ``uv sync --all-extras --dev`` 建立的 :file:`.venv` 環境，以符合指令列"
"開發環境的設定。您也可以讓 PyCharm 建立 Python 環境，但建議優先使用 uv 管理的"
"環境："

#: contributing/start.rst:145
msgid ""
"Don't forget to install the dependencies once the interpreter is set. When "
"using the preferred uv-managed environment, run ``uv sync --all-extras --"
"dev`` from the console."
msgstr ""
"設定直譯器後，別忘了安裝相依套件。使用建議的 uv 管理環境時，請從主控台執行 "
"``uv sync --all-extras --dev``。"

#: contributing/start.rst:149
msgid ""
"The second step is to set the right info to use Django natively inside "
"PyCharm: The idea is to be able to immediately trigger the unit tests in the "
"IDE. For that you need to specify the root path of the Django project and "
"the path to its settings:"
msgstr ""
"第二步是設定正確的資訊來在 PyCharm 中原生使用 Django：理念是能夠立刻觸發 IDE "
"中的單元測試。為此，您需要指定該 Django 專案的根路徑及其設定路徑："

#: contributing/start.rst:155
msgid ""
"Be careful, the `Django project root` is the actual root of the repository, "
"not the Weblate sub-directory. About the settings, you could use "
"the :file:`weblate/settings_test.py` from the repository, but you could "
"create your own setting and set it there."
msgstr ""
"請注意，`Django project root` 是儲存庫的實際根目錄，而不是 Weblate 子目錄。關"
"於設定，您可以使用儲存庫中的 :file:`weblate/settings_test.py`，您也可以建立自"
"己的設定並將其設定在那裡。"

#: contributing/start.rst:159
msgid ""
"The last step is to run the server and to put breakpoints in the code to be "
"able to debug it. This is done by creating a new `Django Server` "
"configuration:"
msgstr ""
"最後一步是執行伺服器，並將中斷點放置在代碼中而能夠除錯它。這通過新增新的 "
"`Django Server` 設定來完成："

#: contributing/start.rst:168
msgid ""
"Be careful with the property called :guilabel:`No reload`: It prevents the "
"server from being reloaded live if you modify files. This allows the "
"existing debugger breakpoints to persist, when they normally would be "
"discarded upon reloading the server."
msgstr ""
"小心被稱為 :guilabel:`No reload` 的屬性：如果您修改檔案，它會阻止伺服器被實時"
"重新載入。這允許保留現有的除錯器中斷點，而它們通常會在重新載入伺服器時被丟"
"棄。"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:2
msgid "Subprojects and embedded code"
msgstr "子專案與嵌入程式碼"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:4
msgid ""
"Weblate would not be possible without other projects it depends on. This "
"document describes how other code is used in Weblate."
msgstr "Weblate 仰賴其他專案才能達成。本文件說明其他程式碼如何用於 Weblate。"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:8
msgid "Vendored frontend code"
msgstr "複製的前端原始碼"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:10
msgid ""
"Weblate vendors several JavaScript libraries. The process is described "
"in :doc:`frontend` and licensing of each vendored library is documented via "
"REUSE as described in :doc:`license`. The up-to-date list of dependencies "
"can be reviewed in :ref:`sbom`."
msgstr ""
"Weblate 內含數個第三方 JavaScript 程式庫。此流程記載於 :doc:`frontend`；各內"
"含程式庫的授權則依 :doc:`license` 所述，透過 REUSE 記錄。最新相依套件清單可"
"在 :ref:`sbom` 檢視。"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:16
msgid "SPDX license data"
msgstr "SPDX 授權資料"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:18
msgid ""
"The SPDX license data is included as a Git submodule in the source code "
"and :file:`weblate/utils/licensedata.py` is generated using :file:`scripts/"
"generate-license-data.py`."
msgstr ""
"SPDX 授權資料以 Git 子模組形式包含在原始碼中，使用 :file:`scripts/generate-"
"license-data.py` 產生 :file:`weblate/utils/licensedata.py`。"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:23
msgid "Test data"
msgstr "測試資料"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:25
msgid ""
"The test repositories in :file:`weblate/trans/tests/data/test-base-"
"repo.*.tar` are generated from https://github.com/WeblateOrg/test, "
"see :ref:`test-data`."
msgstr ""
":file:`weblate/trans/tests/data/test-base-repo.*.tar` 中的測試儲存庫產生自 "
"https://github.com/WeblateOrg/test，見 :ref:`test-data`。"

#: contributing/submodules.rst:31
msgid ""
"Weblate would not be possible without many third-party dependencies. The "
"current dependencies are in :file:`pyproject.toml` and can be reviewed "
"in :ref:`sbom`. The most important dependencies are also described "
"in :ref:`python-deps`."
msgstr ""
"沒有眾多第三方相依套件就不可能有 Weblate。目前相依套件位"
"於 :file:`pyproject.toml` 中，可以在 :ref:`sbom` 中檢視。在 :ref:`python-"
"deps` 中描述了最重要的相依套件。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:2
msgid "Weblate testsuite and continuous integration"
msgstr "Weblate 測試套件與連續整合"

#: contributing/tests.rst:4
msgid ""
"Testsuites exist for most of the current code, increase coverage by adding "
"testcases for any new functionality, and verify that it works."
msgstr ""
"測試套件存在於多數目前代碼，通過為任何新的功能新增測試情況來擴大覆寫範圍，並"
"確認其正常工作。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:10
msgid "Continuous integration"
msgstr "連續整合"

#: contributing/tests.rst:12
msgid ""
"Weblate relies on `GitHub Actions`_ to run tests, build documentation, code "
"linting, and other tasks to ensure code quality."
msgstr ""
"Weblate 仰賴 `GitHub Actions`_ 執行測試、建置說明文件、程式碼檢查及其他工作，"
"以確保程式碼品質。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:15
msgid ""
"`Codecov`_ collects the code coverage information from the tests that were "
"run."
msgstr "`Codecov`_ 從已執行的測試中收集程式碼覆蓋率資訊。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:20
msgid "There are several jobs to verify different aspects:"
msgstr "有幾項工作來確認不同的方面："

#: contributing/tests.rst:22
msgid "Unit and functional tests using `pytest <https://pytest.org/>`_."
msgstr "使用 `pytest <https://pytest.org/>`_ 進行單元與功能測試的。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:23
msgid ""
"Documentation build and external links using `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/>`_."
msgstr ""
"使用 `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-doc.org/>`_ 建置說明文件並檢查外部連結。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:24
msgid ""
"Code linting and quality assurance using `ruff <https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/"
">`_ and `pylint <https://www.pylint.org/>`_."
msgstr ""
"使用 `ruff <https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/>`_ 和 `pylint <https://"
"www.pylint.org/>`_ 的程式碼 lint 和品質保證。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:25
msgid "Code security scanning using `CodeQL <https://codeql.github.com/>`_."
msgstr "使用 `CodeQL <https://codeql.github.com/>`_ 進行程式碼安全掃描。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:26
msgid "Visual changes testing is utilizing `Argos CI <https://argos-ci.com>`_."
msgstr "視覺化變更測試使用 `Argos CI <https://argos-ci.com>`_ 。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:27
msgid ""
"Code formatting using :pypi:`prek`, a faster third-party reimplementation of "
"the `pre-commit <https://pre-commit.com/>`_ framework."
msgstr ""
"使用 :pypi:`prek` 格式化程式碼；這是 `pre-commit <https://pre-commit.com/>`_ "
"框架速度更快的第三方重新實作。"

#: contributing/tests.rst:30
msgid "Migration testing from all supported releases"
msgstr "來自所有支援的發佈版本的合併測試"

#: contributing/tests.rst:31
msgid ""
"Setup verification (ensures that generated dist files do not miss anything "
"and can be tested)"
msgstr "設定確認（確保產生的 dist 檔案不遺失任何內容，並可以測試）"

#: contributing/tests.rst:33
msgid ""
"The configuration for the CI is in :file:`.github/workflows` directory. It "
"heavily uses helper scripts stored in :file:`ci` directory. The scripts can "
"be also executed manually, but they require several environment variables, "
"mostly defining Django settings file to use and test database connection. "
"The example definition of that is in :file:`scripts/test-database.sh`:"
msgstr ""
"CI 設定位於 :file:`.github/workflows` 目錄，並大量使用 :file:`ci` 目錄中的輔"
"助指令碼。這些指令碼也可手動執行，但需要數個環境變數，主要用於指定 Django 設"
"定檔及測試資料庫連線。範例定義位於 :file:`scripts/test-database.sh`："

#: contributing/tests.rst:39
msgid ""
"The Selenium screenshot tests in :file:`weblate/trans/tests/"
"test_selenium.py` serve two purposes. They generate images for visual change "
"testing in CI, and the same images are converted into documentation "
"screenshots by :command:`make -C docs update-screenshots`. Keep screenshot "
"fixtures close to real rendered pages so CI catches UI regressions. When a "
"screenshot includes volatile runtime data, prefer deterministic server-side "
"test inputs over post-render DOM changes."
msgstr ""
":file:`weblate/trans/tests/test_selenium.py` 中的 Selenium 螢幕擷取畫面測試有"
"兩項用途：在 CI 中產生用於視覺變更測試的圖片，並由 :command:`make -C docs "
"update-screenshots` 將相同圖片轉換成說明檔案的螢幕擷取畫面。螢幕擷取畫面固定"
"資料應盡量接近實際呈現的頁面，讓 CI 能找出使用者介面的回歸問題。若螢幕擷取畫"
"面包含不固定的執行階段資料，請優先使用可重現的伺服器端測試輸入，而非在呈現後"
"變更 DOM。"

