#: formats/xliff.rst:42 workflows.rst:59
msgid "Translation states"
msgstr "翻譯狀態"

#: formats/xliff.rst:44
msgid ""
"The ``state`` attribute in the file is partially processed and mapped to the "
"\"Needs edit\" state in Weblate (the following states are used to flag the "
"string as needing edit if there is a target present: ``new``, ``needs-"
"translation``, ``needs-adaptation``, ``needs-l10n``). Should the ``state`` "
"attribute be missing, a string is considered translated as soon as a "
"``<target>`` element exists."
msgstr ""
"檔案中的 ``state`` 屬性會經過部分處理，並對應至 Weblate 的 \"Needs edit\"（需"
"要編輯）狀態（若存在目標內容，下列狀態會將字串標記為需要編輯：``new``、"
"``needs-translation``、``needs-adaptation``、``needs-l10n``）。如果應省略 "
"``state`` 屬性，只要存在 ``<target>`` 元素，就會將字串視為需要翻譯。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:51
msgid ""
"If the translation string has ``approved=\"yes\"``, it will also be imported "
"into Weblate as \"Approved\", anything else will be imported as \"Waiting "
"for review\" (which matches the XLIFF specification)."
msgstr ""
"如果翻譯字串具有 ``approved=\"yes\"`` ，那麼它還將被匯入Weblate 作為"
"\"Approved\"（同意的），任何其它內容被匯入作為\"Waiting for review\" （等待複"
"核，這與XLIFF 規範相符）。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:55
msgid "While saving, Weblate doesn't add those attributes unless necessary:"
msgstr "當儲存時，Weblate 如無必要不會新增其它屬性："

#: formats/xliff.rst:57
msgid ""
"The ``state`` attribute is only added in case string is marked as needing "
"edit."
msgstr "``state`` 屬性只在字串標記為需要編輯的情況下新增。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:58
msgid ""
"The ``approved`` attribute is only added in case string has been reviewed."
msgstr "``approved`` 屬性只在字串已經被複查的情況下新增。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:59
msgid ""
"In other cases the attributes are not added, but they are updated in case "
"they are present."
msgstr "在其它情況下不新增屬性，但在它們出現的情況下更新。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:61
msgid ""
"That means that when using the XLIFF format, it is strongly recommended to "
"turn on the Weblate review process, in order to see and change the approved "
"state of strings."
msgstr ""
"這表示當使用 XLIFF 格式時，強烈建議打開 Weblate 審查過程，從而能看到並變更字"
"串的檢閱狀態。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:64
msgid ""
"Similarly upon importing such files (in the upload form), you should "
"choose :guilabel:`Import as translated` under :guilabel:`Processing of "
"strings needing edit`."
msgstr ""
"相似地在匯入這樣的檔案時（在上傳表格中），應該選擇 :guilabel:`Processing of "
"strings needing edit` 之下的 :guilabel:`Import as translated`。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:73
msgid "Whitespace and newlines in XLIFF"
msgstr "XLIFF 中的空白字元和新行符"

#: formats/xliff.rst:75
msgid ""
"Generally types or amounts of whitespace is not differentiated between in "
"XML formats. If you want to keep it, you have to add the "
"``xml:space=\"preserve\"`` flag to the string."
msgstr ""
"XML 格式通常不區分空白的類型或數量。若要保留空白，必須在字串中加入 "
"``xml:space=\"preserve\"`` 旗標。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:92
msgid "Specifying translation flags"
msgstr "指定翻譯旗標"

#: formats/xliff.rst:94
msgid ""
"You can specify additional translation flags (see :ref:`custom-checks`) by "
"using the ``weblate-flags`` attribute. Weblate also understands ``maxwidth`` "
"and ``font`` attributes from the XLIFF specification:"
msgstr ""
"還可以通過使用 ``weblate-flags`` 屬性指定附加的翻譯標記（請參閱 :ref:`custom-"
"checks`）。 Weblate 還理解來自 XLIFF 規範的 ``maxwidth`` 和 ``font`` 屬性："

#: formats/xliff.rst:107
msgid ""
"The ``font`` attribute is parsed for font family, size and weight, the above "
"example shows all of that, though only font family is required. Any "
"whitespace in the font family is converted to underscore, so ``Source Sans "
"Pro`` becomes ``Source_Sans_Pro``, please keep that in mind when naming the "
"font group (see :ref:`fonts`)."
msgstr ""
"解析 ``font`` 屬性用於字型集、尺寸和粗細，上面的範例顯示了全部，儘管只需要字"
"元集。字元集中的任何空白字元被轉換為下劃線，所以 ``Source Sans Pro`` 變成 "
"``Source_Sans_Pro``，當命名字元集時請記住這些請參閱 :ref:`fonts`）。"

#: formats/xliff.rst:116
msgid ""
